  <refnamediv>
    <refname>rgb2ntsc</refname>
    <refpurpose>This function is used to convert the range of rgb values to the range ntsc values.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   image1 = imread(img);
   image2 = rgb2ntsc(image1);
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>image1:</term>
      <listitem><para> image matrix of the source image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>image2:</term>
      <listitem><para> image matrix of the resultant image.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function takes an rgb image and transforms the channels of the image in accordance with the ntsc values.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
i = imread("lena.jpeg");
rr = rgb2ntsc(i);
imshow(rr(:,:,1));
imshow(rr(:,:,2));
imshow(rr(:,:,3));

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>
</refentry>
